(57, 1, '2013-10-07 11:02:46', '2013-10-07 09:02:46', 'OIM chief executive officer Tjaart Minnaar has 30 years’ experience in organisational performance improvement, industrial relations, and training and development. He advises several South African blue-chip companies and has international consulting experience in areas such as strategic planning, organisational change and development, employee engagement, executive coaching, business structuring, industrial relations and conflict resolution.\r\n\r\nHe has successfully lead several large-scale organisational change processes locally and abroad and has consulted widely in the food, financial services, engineering, construction and mining industries and for parastatals and local government.\r\n<h2>Work Experience</h2>\r\nBefore joining OIM, Tjaart spent 10 years with the Barlow Rand Group’s ICS division where he held various senior human resources positions. While working for subsidiaries such as Table Top, ICS Distribution, Renown and Dairy Maid he gained experience in manufacturing, distribution, wholesale and retail. In the late ’80s he achieved groundbreaking successes in industrial relations, furthering his interest in long-term solutions for organisational performance improvement. It was during this period that he joined forces with OIM founder Professor Robert Tusenius.\r\n<h2>At OIM</h2>\r\nIn 1992 Professor Tusenius invited Tjaart to join OIM as a consultant and a year later he became a director. In 2001 he was appointed MD of OIM Africa, which used to operate in sub-Saharan Africa, and in 2006 he also became MD of the wider OIM Group. Since then he has spearheaded the extension of OIM’s integrated offering into new lines of business and the launch of several new business ventures. Several of his clients has scooped the overall prize and won categories in the Deloitte Best Company To Work For competition. Tjaart’s specific area of interest is the design of large-scale organisational performance improvement processes.\r\n<h2>Qualifications</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>BComm Honours (Industrial Relations) – University of South Africa (1985)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>On A Personal Note</h2>\r\nTjaart enjoys experimenting in the kitchen with different foods, playing a round of golf with his son or travelling with his wife.', 'Tjaart Minnaar', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'tjaart-minnaar', '', '', '2013-10-08 08:54:00', '2013-10-08 06:54:00', '', 0, 'http://192.168.1.11/OIM/website-wp/htdocs/?post_type=team_members&#038;p=57', 0, 'team_members', '', 0),
(58, 1, '2013-10-07 11:00:51', '2013-10-07 09:00:51', '', 'Team', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'acf_team', '', '', '2013-10-07 11:01:21', '2013-10-07 09:01:21', '', 0, 'http://192.168.1.11/OIM/website-wp/htdocs/?post_type=acf&#038;p=58', 0, 'acf', '', 0),
(60, 1, '2013-10-07 11:05:21', '2013-10-07 09:05:21', '<div>\r\n\r\nBusiness performance specialists Operational Improvement Management (OIM) advises several South African blue-chip companies and has managed assignments in Europe, Australia, America and other African countries.\r\n\r\nWith a proven track record dating back to 1985, we specialise in the key areas of people management, organisational improvement and operations management.\r\n\r\nOver the years OIM has developed a unique, integrated approach to business performance management and strategy execution in these areas. We believe our model focuses on the main elements of a successful organisation and provides a framework for:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Strategy definition</li>\r\n	<li>Business architecture and alignment</li>\r\n	<li>Effective leadership and talent management</li>\r\n	<li>Employee relations and stakeholder engagement</li>\r\n	<li>Operations management, optimisation and continuous improvement</li>\r\n	<li>Performance measurement and improvement</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nOur multidisciplinary team offers seamless implementation of these elements, obviating the need for calling in various business consultants with incompatible methodologies and confusing terminologies.\r\n\r\nBut don’t take our word for it – <a href="http://oimgroup.com/clients">read what our clients have to say</a>.\r\n\r\n</div>', 'Overview', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '7-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-10-07 11:05:21', '2013-10-07 09:05:21', '', 7, 'http://192.168.1.11/OIM/website-wp/htdocs/uncategorized/7-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
